&lt;p&gt;As a &lt;strong&gt;Senior Manager, Lead Generation and Marketing Operations &lt;/strong&gt;at TimescaleüêØ, you will be spearheading the development and execution of comprehensive marketing strategies to attract, nurture, and convert potential customers into qualified leads. In this people-management role, you will also be responsible for forecasting and measuring the results of Marketing activities. The ideal candidate is a strategic and creative thinker who has experience with both product-led and sales-led growth motions that target technical audiences in a highly technical industry.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Top candidates will thrive in a fast-paced environment and enjoy the challenge of taking full ownership and responsibility for effective campaigns that generate qualified leads and trial signups.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your main responsibilities will include:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Setting the overall strategy, goals, forecasts, and budget for lead generation, nurturing, and scoring in partnership and alignment with Sales goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Using performance insights and competitive/market analysis to plan and manage the execution of lead-gen and trial signup campaigns that leverage the full scope of marketing programs, including email nurture, landing pages, paid ads, events, and webinars.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyzing marketing metrics and campaign performance to make data-driven decisions, continually optimizing on CPL and growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working with the Content Strategy team to develop content assets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Overseeing the effective use of our marketing tech stack, including Hubspot and Common Room, and using Salesforce for lead management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This role is remote with an ideal location in the United States, and English language fluency is a requirement.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A little bit about you&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You are a self-starter who finds great fulfillment in getting things done‚Äîwhether it‚Äôs planning a lead-gen campaign, creating a paid ad to drive trial signups, or developing a new operational process‚Äîand seeing the impact of your work. You are not intimidated by a fast-moving and multi-tasking environment but rather revel in the opportunity to move quickly with autonomy. You believe that working as a team can improve your output, you are awesome but humble, and folks look forward to working with you. You‚Äôre experienced with marketing a technical product to technical audiences and working collaboratively and effectively with stakeholders, developers, and designers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You also have:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of experience in B2B SaaS marketing with a focus on lead generation, nurture, and qualification process. Highly technical product experience is a must; database and/or cloud experience is preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong strategic thinking and ability to tie lead-gen activities to overall company goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated success in utilizing HubSpot and Salesforce for marketing automation and lead management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong expertise in paid ads, including Google and LinkedIn.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ability to strategize, concept, create, and scale projects with autonomy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An analytical mind with enthusiasm for problem-solving and measuring effectiveness.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expert-level organizational, analytical, and written/verbal communication skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;By applying for this position, you are agreeing to &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.timescale.com/legal/timescale-applicant-privacy-notice&quot;&gt;Timescale&#39;s Applicant Privacy Notice.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
